# Part 2 — Describe a person who encouraged you to protect nature

One person who really encouraged me to protect nature is my high school biology teacher, Mr. Li. He wasn’t the kind of teacher who only focused on textbooks and exams. Instead, he often talked about real environmental problems, such as climate change, plastic pollution, and deforestation. His lessons were always inspiring because he connected science with our daily lives.

What impressed me most was that he encouraged us through his own actions rather than just giving lectures. For example, he always carried a reusable water bottle and refused to use disposable chopsticks or plastic bags. He even organized volunteer activities where students cleaned parks and picked up litter near rivers. I joined one of those activities during my final year of high school, and it completely changed my attitude toward environmental protection.

He especially encouraged us to reduce unnecessary waste and develop environmentally friendly habits. For instance, he suggested using public transportation more often, saving electricity, and recycling paper whenever possible. At first, I thought these small actions wouldn’t make much difference, but he explained that if millions of people made small changes, the overall impact would actually be huge.

I really admire this teacher because he made environmental protection feel practical instead of abstract. Thanks to him, I’ve become much more aware of my daily habits. Even now, I still try to live in a more sustainable way, such as bringing my own shopping bag and avoiding single-use products whenever I can.

### 中文翻译：

真正鼓励我保护自然的人是我的高中生物老师李老师。他并不是那种只关注课本和考试的老师，相反，他经常和我们讨论现实中的环境问题，比如气候变化、塑料污染以及森林砍伐。他的课总是很有启发性，因为他会把科学知识和日常生活联系起来。

最让我印象深刻的是，他并不是只会说教，而是通过自己的行动来影响我们。比如，他总是随身携带可重复使用的水杯，也拒绝使用一次性筷子和塑料袋。他甚至组织过志愿活动，带学生去公园和河边捡垃圾。我在高中最后一年参加过一次这样的活动，那次经历彻底改变了我对环境保护的看法。

他尤其鼓励我们减少浪费，养成环保习惯。例如，他建议我们更多乘坐公共交通、节约用电以及尽量回收纸张。起初我觉得这些小事没什么作用，但他告诉我们，如果数百万人都做出一点改变，最终带来的影响会非常巨大。

我非常敬佩这位老师，因为他让环保变得具体而真实，而不是一个空洞的概念。也正因为他，我现在会更加注意自己的生活习惯，比如自带购物袋，尽量避免使用一次性用品。

